import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['ret'].hist()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of daily returns?")
    plt.xlabel("Daily Returns")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['open'], data['close'])
    plt.xlabel('Open Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Close Prices')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between open and close prices?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    avg_ret_by_signal = data.groupby('signal')['ret'].mean()
    
    ax = avg_ret_by_signal.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average daily return for each signal type?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;
